@startuml
title Mesh Buffer Upload - Sequence View

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

participant "RenderCommand" as Command
participant "Mesh" as Mesh
participant "OpenGLRenderContext" as Context
participant "OpenGLGPUDataBufferCenter" as BufferCenter
participant "OpenGLVertexBufferObject" as VBO
participant "OpenGLIndexBufferObject" as IBO
participant "OpenGLVertexArrayObject" as VAO
participant "OpenGLDrawElementsCommand" as Draw

Command -> Mesh : vertices() and indices()
Command -> Context : request GPU buffers for mesh
Context -> BufferCenter : get or create mesh buffers
BufferCenter -> VBO : upload vertex bytes
BufferCenter -> IBO : upload index bytes
BufferCenter -> VAO : configure vertex layout
Command -> VAO : bind()
Command -> Draw : execute primitive draw
Draw -> Context : glDrawElements

note bottom
Mesh commands convert stable CPU mesh data into OpenGL
buffer objects before issuing draw calls.
end note

@enduml
